HEADWORD: Poinder
<hw>Poind"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The keeper of a cattle pound; a pinder.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>  <rj><au>T. Adams.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who distrains property.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>  <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poinsettia</ent>⟦br⟧
